### File Descriptions
```
app.py
- The main backend Python application file using a web framework (e.g., Flask).
- Handles routing for all nine pages, data reading/writing from/to local text files in the 'data' directory.
- Implements business logic for browsing, ordering, cart management, checkout, order tracking, and reviews.
- Since the application is not very complex, all backend logic is consolidated here for maintainability.

templates/
- Contains HTML template files for each page defined in the requirements.
- Each HTML file corresponds to one of the nine pages plus an additional page for writing reviews.
- Templates use placeholders to dynamically render data passed from app.py.

static/
- Contains static assets such as CSS stylesheets, JavaScript files, and images.
- CSS for styling the web pages.
- JavaScript for client-side interactivity (e.g., button actions, filtering).
- Images folder stores restaurant logos and menu item photos referenced in the UI.

data/
- Stores all application data in text files as specified.
- Each file corresponds to a data entity (restaurants, menus, cart, orders, order items, deliveries, reviews).
- The backend reads from and writes to these files to persist application state.
```"

